<br />
When servers came up from the thursday patch I immediately headed to HS, as I had a full pack worth of wailing and no shrieking.  First  attack that came up was grimlings to owlbear cave.  Myself and two guildies headed there, and in transit a second attack on the owllbear cave was declared by the wolves.  My guildies and I took out the bears just as the grimlings were arriving, the grimlings took over the camp, and then the wolves came in unopposed 2 minutes later and took control of north away from them.  (i.e. if a second attack occurs while one is in progress, no second set of defenders will spawn)<br />
<br />
And of course, a couple hours later all my work manipulating the zone was ruined by the emergency patch.</div>
